  "name": "RPlog_Interrogation_Training_Day_1_-_Liza_Molokai",
  "title": "Interrogation Resistance Training, Day One",
  "summary": "As a brutal ISB resistance-training exercise overseen by Sector Director Korynn Fleming, two loyal Imperial officers, the pilot Liza Molokai and the injured Petty Officer Xy'lear Dagnmith, are subjected to sensory torture, sleep deprivation, and staged horrors to test and harden their loyalty. The pair are thrown together in a humiliation chamber and forced to watch as disguised rebel prisoners and their supposed families are executed before them when they refuse to betray the Empire. Both endure the ordeal with defiance, fighting CompForce troopers with fists and chains until they are subdued and chained to the wall. Korynn judges their performance adequate, slapping Liza for momentarily turning away and instructing her that pleading for an injured comrade reveals exploitable weakness, while praising Xy'lear's willingness to fight against impossible odds. Satisfied, Korynn orders their injuries treated and rewards them with a warm meal as the day's training concludes.",
